newsitem.title: TAIWAN: Taiwan to tender for 108,000T U.S. soybeans.
newsitem.headline: Taiwan to tender for 108,000T U.S. soybeans.

text.p: Taiwan's Breakfast Soybean Procurement Association plans to tender on Friday for two shipments of U.S. soybeans totalling 108,000 tonnes, traders said on Thursday.
The first shipment would be slated for delivery from the U.S. Gulf of Mexico November 10-24 or from the Pacific Northwest November 25-December 9, they said.
The second would be slated for delivery from the U.S. Gulf December 5-19 or from the Pacific Northwest December 20-January 3, they said.
